summary: After five years of treatment, my last therapy appointment was today.[[MORE]] I remember being a freshman, I begged my mom to...
caption:
After five years of treatment, my last therapy appointment was today.

I remember being a freshman, I begged my mom to take me because I knew I needed it.
Skip to my first appointment, where I told my therapist I saw no hope for myself or the future.
My therapist was the first person I told in detail about my abuse, and she was the first one to believe me. She helped me open up to others, and tell them how I feel, and when I needed help.

She showed me new coping mechanisms, to help me when I was having a panic attack, or when I was in a trauma situation, which unfortunately was often.
She had me write about my abuse, to help me process it.
She is the reason I don’t shiver when I hear my abusers name anymore.
She is the one that recognized my mental illness was a disability, and gave me medication that made me feel alive again.
She is one of the reasons I have never been hospitalized or have not tried to commit suicide.
She was the one who encouraged me to go back to a better school with my caring friends, graduate on time, get a job, and move out of my abusive home, which I hope to do in less then two weeks.

I painted this for her, over the course of 4 days and gave it to her today.
I’m happy to say she said it was beautiful, and planned to frame it.

If you do not go to therapy because you are scared, or you don’t think it would help, I highly suggest going and finding yourself a good therapist.
My therapist changed my life for the better.
Without her, I’m not sure i’d be here to tell you all this.
Please, be sure to tell your therapists thank you the next time you see them, and feel free to show them this. 

Thank you, forever and always, Lynn.
